meta {
  name: Mass-Assign 03 Verify Victim Untouched
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

get {
  url: {{host}}/v1/surveys/sec_victim
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

assert {
  res.status: eq 200
  res.body.name: eq sec_victim
}

docs {
  THE security assertion. After the mass-assign attack in seq 4, the victim
  survey row must still be reachable by its original name and must still
  carry that name.

  Pre-fix: createFromData clobbered the row's name to "PWNED" via the
  unfiltered assignProperties → save round-trip, so this GET 404s and the
  test fails (red).
  Post-fix: settings is allowlisted to the legitimate config columns and
  id/name/user_id/results_table can no longer be smuggled through, so the
  victim row is untouched and this GET succeeds (green).
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: false
  timeout: 0
}
